  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why is my battle.net region locked to China?",
  "response": "If your **Battle.net** account is region-locked to **China**, it could be due to one or more of the following reasons:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Account Creation Location**\n   - If you created your Battle.net account while physically located in **China**, Blizzard may have automatically assigned your account to the **China region**. This is common for players in mainland China due to Blizzard's partnership with **NetEase**, the company that operates Blizzard games in China.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **ID Verification**\n   - In China, Blizzard requires players to verify their identity using a **Chinese ID number** or **phone number**. If you provided such information during account creation or verification, your account could be locked to the China region.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Payment Method**\n   - If you used a **Chinese payment method** (e.g., Alipay, WeChat Pay, or a Chinese bank account) to purchase games or subscriptions, Blizzard may have associated your account with the China region.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **IP Address**\n   - If you accessed Battle.net from a **Chinese IP address** during account creation or significant changes, Blizzard may have locked your account to the China region based on your location.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **China-Specific Licensing**\n   - Blizzard games in China are operated by **NetEase**, and the versions of games in China are often different from the global versions due to local regulations. If you purchased or installed a China-specific version of a game, your account may be locked to the China region.\n\n---\n\n### How to Resolve or Change Your Region\n1. **Contact Blizzard Support**:\n   - Reach out to **Blizzard Customer Support** and explain your situation. They may be able to help you change your region or unlock your account, though this may require verification of your identity and location.\n\n2. **Create a New Account**:\n   - If you cannot change the region of your existing account, you may need to create a new Battle.net account while physically located outside of China or using a VPN to mask your location.\n\n3. **Use a VPN**:\n   - Access Battle.net via a VPN set to a location outside of China to avoid being region-locked. However, this is not a permanent solution and may violate Blizzard's terms of service.\n\n4. **Check Local Regulations**:\n   - If you are in China, you may need to accept that your account will be region-locked due to local laws and Blizzard's partnership with NetEase.\n\n---\n\n### Important Notes\n- **China-region accounts cannot be transferred** to global regions due to licensing and operational differences.\n- Blizzard and NetEase temporarily suspended services in China in January 2023, so if you're in China, you may need to wait for further updates or use alternative methods to access Blizzard games.\n\nIf you need further assistance, contacting **Blizzard Support** is your best option.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
